n          Plus, the AI tell that’s exploded in company documents, a skill for creating product videos, and comics \r\n         ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌ ‌\r\n      </div>\r\n\r\n    <table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" align=\"center\" role=\"presentation\"><tr><td>\r\n      <div class=\"article\" role=\"article\" aria-label=\"Model Wars\" lang=\"en\">\r\n\r\n          <!-- Main content section. Main is a useful landmark element. -->\r\n          <main>\r\n            <a class=\"logo\" href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvLyIsInBvc2l0aW9uIjowfQ==\">\r\n              <img class=\"logo-img\" width=\"84\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/static/every-logo.png\">\r\n            </a>\r\n            \r\n<div class=\"newsletter-email\">\r\n  <div class=\"post-intro\">\r\n      <div class=\"publication-brand\">\r\n        <a class=\"publication-brand-link\" href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL2NvbnRleHQtd2luZG93IiwicG9zaXRpb24iOjF9\">\r\n            <img class=\"publication-logo\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" src=\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/publication/logo/94/small_context_windown_1.png\">\r\n            <p class=\"publication-name\">Context Window</p>\r\n        </a>\r\n      </div>\r\n    <h1 class=\"title\">\r\n        <a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL2NvbnRleHQtd2luZG93L21vZGVsLXdhcnMiLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6Mn0=\">Model <span class=\"hand hand-W\">W</span>ars</a>\r\n    </h1>\r\n      <h2 class=\"subtitle\">\r\n          <a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL2NvbnRleHQtd2luZG93L21vZGVsLXdhcnMiLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6M30=\">Plus, the AI tell that’s exploded in company documents, a skill for creating product videos, and comics </a>\r\n      </h2>\r\n    <div class=\"post-meta\">\r\n        <p class=\"byline\">by <a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL0BsYXVyYV8yN2JiYWZfMSIsInBvc2l0aW9uIjo0fQ==\">Laura Entis</a></p>\r\n    </div>\r\n      <figure>\r\n        <img class=\"post-cover\" src=\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/post/cover/4131/full_page_cover_CW_-_Thursday.png\" width=\"600\">\r\n          <figcaption>Midjourney/Every illustration.</figcaption>\r\n      </figure>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n  <div class=\"post-body\">\r\n    <p><em>GPT 5.5 is here, and OpenAI’s latest model has it all. It’s fast enough to use constantly, personable enough to collaborate with, and assertive enough to carry a plan through serious engineering work. If you didn’t catch our full review, including benchmark results, Reach Test ratings, pricing, screenshots, and advice on when to reach for GPT-5.5 versus <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL3ZpYmUtY2hlY2svb3B1cy00LTciLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6NX0=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Opus 4.7</a></u>, read our <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL3ZpYmUtY2hlY2svZ3B0LTUtNSIsInBvc2l0aW9uIjo2fQ==\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Vibe Check</a></u> or rewatch the <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy55b3V0dWJlLmNvbS93YXRjaD92PUdST3QxTmQ0YXNZIiwicG9zaXRpb24iOjd9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">livestream</a></u>, where we grilled OpenAI’s </em><strong><em>Dominik Kundel</em></strong><em> and </em><strong><em>Romain Huet</em></strong><em> on how they’re using the model. </em></p>\r\n<p><em>But how will that shift the balance between OpenAI and Anthropic? That may be a product question as much as a model question. Every engineer </em><strong><em><u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL0BuaXR5ZXNoIiwicG9zaXRpb24iOjh9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Nityesh Agarwal</a></u></em></strong><em> and </em><strong><em><u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL21vbm9sb2d1ZS50byIsInBvc2l0aW9uIjo5fQ==\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Monologue</a></u></em></strong><em> general manager </em><strong><em><u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL0BuYXZlZW5fNjgwNCIsInBvc2l0aW9uIjoxMH0=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Naveen Naidu</a></u></em></strong><em> weigh in.—<u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL0BrYXRlXzE3NjciLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6MTF9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Kate Lee</a></u></em></p>\r\n<div class=\"quill-button\" data-source='{\"id\":\"quill-button-1777038350559\",\"text\":\"Subscribe\",\"url\":\"https://every.to/subscribe?source=post_button\"}' id=\"quill-button-1777038350559\"><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL3N1YnNjcmliZT9zb3VyY2U9cG9zdF9idXR0b24iLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6MTJ9\">Subscribe</a></div>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<hr class=\"quill-line\">\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>Inside Every</h2>\r\n<h4>Codex versus Claude Code</h4>\r\n<p>This week, Anthropic tested removing Claude Code from the <u><a href=\"https://every.\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">$20 Claude Pro plan</a></u>, prompting an outcry from users and <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3guY29tL3Roc290dGlhdXgvc3RhdHVzLzIwNDY3NDA3NTkwNTYxNjI4MTYiLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6MTR9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">drawing</a></u> <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3guY29tL3NhbWEvc3RhdHVzLzIwNDY4MDgxMTQ1NjE5NzQ1NjciLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6MTV9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">jabs</a></u> from OpenAI executives on X, perhaps feeling emboldened by the big launch they knew was coming. </p>\r\n<p>The exchange kicked off a Slack debate between <strong><u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL0BuaXR5ZXNoIiwicG9zaXRpb24iOjE2fQ==\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Nityesh Agarwal</a></u></strong>, our resident Claude Code devotee, and <strong><u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL0BuYXZlZW5fNjgwNCIsInBvc2l0aW9uIjoxN30=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Naveen Naidu</a></u></strong>, who rides hard for OpenAI’s coding app Codex. </p>\r\n<p><strong>Nityesh’s take:</strong> Anthropic potentially raising prices is <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3guY29tL25pdHllc2hhZ2Evc3RhdHVzLzIwNDY4MTgwMjY5MzU0MTkyNjM_cz0yMCIsInBvc2l0aW9uIjoxOH0=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">“simple market economics”</a></u>—there is a huge demand for Claude products because they’re the best available, so they can charge more. On the other hand, OpenAI’s response underscores how frustrated the company has become playing catch-up as it scrambles to replicate <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL3NvdXJjZS1jb2RlL2hvdy1pLXVzZS1jbGF1ZGUtY29kZS10by1zaGlwLWxpa2UtYS10ZWFtLW9mLWZpdmUiLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6MTl9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Claude Code</a></u>, <u><a href=\"https://every.\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Cowork</a></u>, and <u><a href=\"https://every.\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">skills</a></u>. From a product standpoint, Claude in the browser and the Claude Code command line interface (CLI) are better than ChatGPT and Codex.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Naveen’s response:</strong> Anthropic’s models are powerful, but they also burn through way too much compute in production. OpenAI is much stronger on infrastructure, and GPT 5.5 is a <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL29wZW5haS5jb20vaW5kZXgvaW50cm9kdWNpbmctZ3B0LTUtNS8iLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6MjJ9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">token-efficient model</a></u>. And while it’s true Anthropic is first to market with a lot of products and features, including computer use—which allows AI to operate your computer on your behalf—OpenAI is better at execution. Naveen consistently reaches for ChatGPT and the Codex desktop app, while he finds the Claude Code app too buggy to spend any time in. </p>\r\n<p><strong>Where they agree:</strong> The Claude Code app is, indeed, bad—Nityesh concedes he only uses the CLI. And both labs misjudged how much compute they would need, but in opposite directions: Anthropic is <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5idXNpbmVzc2luc2lkZXIuY29tL2FpLWNvbXB1dGUtbGltaXRzLWFudGhyb3BpYy1naXRodWItMjAyNi00IiwicG9zaXRpb24iOjIzfQ==\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">struggling to keep up with demand</a></u>, whereas OpenAI has <u><a href=\"https://every.\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">invested</a></u> heavily in infrastructure and is now scrambling to get people to use its products. </p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<hr class=\"quill-line\">\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>Data point</h2>\r\n<h4>It’s not just a grammatical pattern; it’s an AI tell </h4>\r\n<p>Four times.</p>\r\n<p>That’s how much the usage of “not just a ___, it’s a ___” sentence construction rose in large U.S. company documents between 2023 and 2025, <u><a href=\"https://every.\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">per Barrons</a></u>. </p>\r\n<div class=\"quill-block-image\" id=\"quill-block-image-1777039315687-0pyg1kvcp\" data-source='{\"dom_id\":\"quill-block-image-1777039315687-0pyg1kvcp\",\"link\":\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/editor/posts/4131/optimized_66308451-2d9b-4604-abdf-46b09e95ec04.png\",\"image\":\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/editor/posts/4131/optimized_66308451-2d9b-4604-abdf-46b09e95ec04.png\",\"caption\":\"The rise in correlative constructions neatly tracks with the adoption of LLMs. (Source: Barrons.)\",\"error\":null}'><div>\r\n<a href=\"https://every.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/editor/posts/4131/optimized_66308451-2d9b-4604-abdf-46b09e95ec04.png\" alt=\"The rise in correlative constructions neatly tracks with the adoption of LLMs. (Source: Barrons.)\" width=\"600\"></a><figcaption class=\"quill-image-caption\">The rise in correlative constructions neatly tracks with the adoption of LLMs. (Source: Barrons.)</figcaption>\r\n</div></div>\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n<p>Like the em dash, the correlative constructions are so beloved by LLMs that human writers now avoid them so as not to be accused of writing with AI. </p>\r\n<p>Hot take alert: That’s a bummer. The great profile writer <strong>Taffy Brodesser-Akner</strong>’s work is teeming with them. Or it was, pre-ChatGPT. Her <u><a href=\"https://every.\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">2018 </a></u><em><u><a href=\"https://every.\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">New York Times Magazine</a></u></em><u><a href=\"https://every.\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"> feature on Goop</a></u> uses some version of “not X, it’s Y” in almost every other paragraph.</p>\r\n<p>I doubt even a writer as beloved as Taffy could get away with that today. It’s not that her trademark style is any less effective—it’s that no one would believe she wrote it.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<hr class=\"quill-line\">\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>Steal this workflow</h2>\r\n<h4>How to (almost) one-shot a product video</h4>\r\n<p>After days of battling open-source video creation tool <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5yZW1vdGlvbi5kZXYvIiwicG9zaXRpb24iOjMwfQ==\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Remotion</a></u> and Claude Code, trying to one-shot a video for a product relaunch, <strong><u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL0B0ZWRlc2NhdSIsInBvc2l0aW9uIjozMX0=\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Austin Tedesco</a></u></strong>, Every’s head of growth, figured out how to get a polished clip. Here’s the workflow he runs any time he needs a social video for a product launch or feature demo, like the one he created for the <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3guY29tL2RhbnNoaXBwZXIvc3RhdHVzLzIwNDQwNzkyNTU3MjY4MzgyNzMiLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6MzJ9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">relaunch of </a></u><strong><u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3guY29tL2RhbnNoaXBwZXIvc3RhdHVzLzIwNDQwNzkyNTU3MjY4MzgyNzMiLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6MzN9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Sparkle</a></u></strong>, our agent-native app that cleans and organizes files on your Mac. </p>\r\n<div class=\"quill-block-image\" id=\"quill-block-image-1777042351710\" data-source=\"{&quot;dom_id&quot;:&quot;quill-block-image-1777042351710&quot;,&quot;link&quot;:&quot;https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/editor/posts/4131/optimized_931b81a8-d8b8-4615-8981-99168b9b8533.gif&quot;,&quot;image&quot;:&quot;https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/editor/posts/4131/optimized_931b81a8-d8b8-4615-8981-99168b9b8533.gif&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A GIF showing a clip from Austin' s product video. (Source: Every.)&quot;,&quot;error&quot;:null}\"><div>\r\n<a href=\"https://every.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/editor/posts/4131/optimized_931b81a8-d8b8-4615-8981-99168b9b8533.gif\" alt=\"A GIF showing a clip from Austin' s product video. (Source: Every.)\" width=\"600\"></a><figcaption class=\"quill-image-caption\">A GIF showing a clip from Austin' s product video. (Source: Every.)</figcaption>\r\n</div></div>\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1: Screen-record yourself using the product you’re doing a clip on.</strong> All you need is raw footage of yourself clicking through features in real time. </p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2: Send the recording to a model—Austin prefers Opus—and have it draft a storyboard.</strong> The recording provides a ground truth for how the UI works and what the copy says. This prevents the most frequent cause of fake-looking launch videos: plausible-but-hallucinated labels and features.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3: Iterate on the storyboard.</strong> Go back and forth with the model until the hook, pacing, and beat-by-beat plan feel right. </p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 4: Hand the storyboard to a coding agent and have it build the video in Remotion.</strong> With the screen recording and the corresponding storyboard, the first full render is usually publishable. It’s not a true one-shot, but it saves a lot of time. </p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<hr class=\"quill-line\">\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>Now, next, nixed</h2>\r\n<h4>Prompts are the new installers</h4>\r\n<p>Companies and developers are trying a new way to let users download an AI tool. Instead of asking them to press a download button, users copy a setup prompt, paste it into Claude Code or Codex, and let the agent install the tool.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Now</strong>:<strong> Copy prompt, paste, install</strong>. This is how we install Every’s agent-native document editor <strong><u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5wcm9vZmVkaXRvci5haS8iLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6MzV9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Proof</a></u></strong>: Paste a prompt into your assistant, and it handles the setup. The prompt is doing the job the download button used to do: It gets the user from “I want to try this” to “It’s running in my workflow.”</p>\r\n<p><strong>Next: Someone designs the standard version of this. </strong>The copyable prompt block becomes a normal part of product pages and GitHub READMEs (the instructions for software projects), especially for developer tools. It should work on the web and on a repository homepage, and feel as obvious as a “Sign in with Google” button.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Nixed: The download button as the main way in. </strong>The old-school way of installing software—clicking a download link and running a setup file—still makes sense when software requires direct hardware access or needs to work offline, but for AI-native tools, the front door is: Copy this prompt into your agent.<em>—<u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL0BrYXRpZS5wYXJyb3R0MTIiLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6MzZ9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Katie Parrott</a></u></em></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<hr class=\"quill-line\">\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>Model happenings</h2>\r\n<h4>News you might have missed</h4>\r\n<ul><li>\r\n<strong>Cowork <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3guY29tL2NsYXVkZWFpL3N0YXR1cy8yMDQ2MzI4NjE5MjQ5Njg0OTg5P3M9NDYiLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6Mzd9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">shipped live artifacts</a></u>.</strong> Claude can build dashboards and trackers inside your workspace that pull fresh data from your apps and refresh each time you open them—pouring narrative gasoline on the <u><a href=\"https://every.\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">SaaSpocalypse fire</a></u>. </li></ul>\r\n<div class=\"quill-block-image\" id=\"quill-block-image-1777039945247\" data-source='{\"dom_id\":\"quill-block-image-1777039945247\",\"link\":\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/editor/posts/4131/optimized_64a77cf4-debd-4ae8-b8eb-bc5d249b5858.png\",\"image\":\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/editor/posts/4131/optimized_64a77cf4-debd-4ae8-b8eb-bc5d249b5858.png\",\"caption\":\"Cowork artifacts allow you to create the dashboards and data reporting visualizations tools like ChartMogul provide. (Image courtesy of Brandon Gell.)\",\"error\":null}'><div>\r\n<a href=\"https://every.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/editor/posts/4131/optimized_64a77cf4-debd-4ae8-b8eb-bc5d249b5858.png\" alt=\"Cowork artifacts allow you to create the dashboards and data reporting visualizations tools like ChartMogul provide. (Image courtesy of Brandon Gell.)\" width=\"600\"></a><figcaption class=\"quill-image-caption\">Cowork artifacts allow you to create the dashboards and data reporting visualizations tools like ChartMogul provide. (Image courtesy of Brandon Gell.)</figcaption>\r\n</div></div>\r\n<p><br></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<strong>OpenAI gave Codex <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2RldmVsb3BlcnMub3BlbmFpLmNvbS9jb2RleC9tZW1vcmllcy9jaHJvbmljbGUiLCJwb3NpdGlvbiI6NDB9\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">screen memory</a></u>.</strong> Codex now retains what’s on your screen across tabs and sessions, so you don’t have to re-paste context every time you start a new task. </li>\r\n<li>\r\n<strong>OpenAI launched <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3guY29tL29wZW5haS9zdGF0dXMvMjA0NzAwODk4NzY2NTgwOTc3MT9zPTQ2IiwicG9zaXRpb24iOjQxfQ==\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">workspace agents</a></u> in ChatGPT.</strong> The Codex-powered feature lets teams create custom shared agents that can pull information from different sources, analyze it, and turn it into a draft or next step. It’s another signal that <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL2V2ZXJ5LnRvL2NvbnRleHQtd2luZG93L3lvdS1yZS10aGUtYnJlYWQtaW4tdGhlLWFpLXNhbmR3aWNoIiwicG9zaXRpb24iOjQyfQ==\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">agents are becoming a shared team resource</a></u>, rather than purely individual AI assistants. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<hr class=\"quill-line\">\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>One last thing</h2>\r\n<h4>Nityesh has been having a lot of fun with ChatGPT Images 2.0 </h4>\r\n<p>A couple of his recent creations include a vintage poster to celebrate the release of  <u><a href=\"https://every.\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Monologue Notes</a></u>, a new feature in our agent-native recording app, and an infographic about securing <u><a href=\"https://every.to/emails/click/2ee614b6e6ffd755717ebf28ff1eab3890d62a8deb4d17e7b804a462d939eb11/eyJzdWJqZWN0IjoiTW9kZWwgV2FycyIsInBvc3RfaWQiOjQxMzEsInBvc3RfdHlwZSI6InBvc3QiLCJ1cmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy55b3V0dWJlLmNvbS93YXRjaD92PUxHOTQzTVgtS3JnIiwicG9zaXRpb24iOjQ0fQ==\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Claudie</a></u>, the consulting team’s always-on AI employee. </p>\r\n<div class=\"quill-block-image\" id=\"quill-block-image-1777040011853\" data-source='{\"dom_id\":\"quill-block-image-1777040011853\",\"link\":\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/editor/posts/4131/optimized_59522edf-a43c-45fe-b6bd-8842cbc99c46.png\",\"image\":\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/editor/posts/4131/optimized_59522edf-a43c-45fe-b6bd-8842cbc99c46.png\",\"caption\":\"The prompt: Turn Monologue Notes’s landing page into a vintage poster. (Image courtesy of Nityesh Agarwal)\",\"error\":null}'><div>\r\n<a href=\"https://every.\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://d24ovhgu8s7341.cloudfront.net/uploads/editor/posts/4131/optimized_59522edf-a43c-45fe-b6bd-8842cbc99c46.png\" alt=\"The prompt: Turn Monologue Notes’s landing page into a vintage poster. (Image courtesy of Nityesh Agarwal)\" width=\"600\"></a><figcaption class=\"quill-image-caption\">The prompt: Turn Monologue Notes’s landing page into a vintage poster. (Image courtesy of Nityesh Agarwal)</figcaption